        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-11T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="348" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.00/3–1147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-11T17:00:00+08:00">March 11, 1947—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 11—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>520. It is reported here that “committee to settle February 28 incident” at
                    Taipei on March 8 submitted to Governor Chen Yi 32 resolutions for acceptance,
                    including: Enactment autonomous constitution; election by people of mayor and
                    magistrates before June; right of assembly, freedom of press and right to
                    strike; forbidding political arrests; provincehood for Taiwan; abolition Taiwan
                    garrison headquarters; and pending approval Central Government, administrative
                    bureau of settlement committee to undertake temporary reorganization Taiwan
                    administration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
